in view of the galloping technical progress that threatens to transform our comfortable home into high @-@ tech switchgear centers , our columnist Bernd Matthies dissolves with a highly familiar electronic accessory .
as I write this here , my view of the spiral cable connecting the listener to the phone falls , and I think : Boah , how retro is it ?
but there is one thought behind this : if the cable were not there , all the listeners would fly around in the house without hesitation , and that would be much more retro .
anyway , the eceltronic ( eceltronic ?
no , typing errors : electronic ) sector the rule that today &apos;s world novelty is tomorrow &apos;s electric scrap - outdated .
and those who still have a tube TV in the living room today , for example , simply say that they reject television in principle .
why these considerations ?
because the ifa &apos;s applets on the radio tower this week once again show us our absolute incompetence in electronic matters .
the shop , which used to be blindly controlled by a washing machine and CD player , does not even understand the purpose of the devices that are spread out in front of him with an unfathomable whim of experts : &quot; connected Home , Wearables , Health Care and Urban Technologies &quot; promises us the press office .
yes , is it ?
what should we talk to people who apparently voluntarily spread such Quark ?
in fact , for some 20 years , the main issue has been that we should link up our house .
so that the yoghurt itself can be ordered , so that the fire detector tells us on holiday on the Maldives that it burns in the working room .
and would it not be wonderful if we had air conditioning from the office on our early arrival ... ?
yes , that requires air conditioning .
but a dream will certainly come true soon : we lift our watch , say it &quot; sucking ! &quot; - and at home the vacuum cleaner is out .
wrong .
everything amounts to nothing less than a revolution : &quot; the boundaries between white and brown goods are blurred , &quot; an industry expert racks , you can connect the washing machine with a headphone , the steam garer sends the weather report and the data bricks show how long the pizza in the oven still takes , but nothing is useful .
we also know from day @-@ to @-@ day practice : if a new @-@ fashioned device is needed urgently , the battery is guaranteed to be empty .
another reason is that the spiral cable on the phone will survive the next radio exhibitions .
Israeli children return to school after the war in Gaza
thousands of Israeli children from the areas near the Gaza Strip returned to school on Monday after spending the summer in air protection areas , while rocket and murderers struck their communities during the 50 @-@ day war between Israel and Hamas , and the Gaza schools remained closed , while the area recovered from the fighting .
the start of the school brought a sense of joy and expectation to the communities of rockets in southern Israel , but the signs of fighting are still fresh .
in the southern town of Ashdod , staff of the &quot; Pashosh &quot; kindergarten , who was hit by a rocket , arrived before the students arrived from the walls and shooting walls .
&quot; we are a bit afraid , but are excited , &quot; said Ronit Bart , resident in Kibutz Saad and there English teacher .
many children from our area urgently need a return to a routine .
her 11 @-@ year @-@ old daughter Shani Bart said it feels &quot; a bit funny &quot; to suddenly go back to school .
&quot; these were difficult times , and we did not leave the House at all , &quot; she said .
President Reuven Rivlin visited Kibbbutz near the Gaza border to offer his support .
