many of the inhabitants of Nahal Oz , a community near the border with Gaza where a 4 @-@ year @-@ old boy was killed by a Palestinian mortar grenade , are still reluctant to return .
the Ministry of Education announced that around a dozen families have not yet returned .
their children were temporarily accommodated in other schools .
Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu attended a school in Sderot , a border city with Gaza , which is heavily influenced by Palestinian terror .
he called on the children to learn a lot and said , &quot; We will make sure that they acquire knowledge and offer you security . &quot;
Israel and Hamas agreed last Tuesday on an indefinite ceasefire .
the cease @-@ fire caused an immediate end to the fighting , but important issues remain unresolved , such as Hamas &apos;s call for the lifting of the Israeli @-@ Egyptian blockade of Gaza and the re @-@ opening of air and sea ports in Gaza .
Israel calls for the disarmament of Hamas and the handover of the bodies of two Israeli soldiers killed in the fighting .
a new round of indirect talks is expected to start this month in Egypt .
in the war , more than 2,100 Palestinians were killed , three quarters of them civilians , and at least 494 children , according to estimates from the Palestinians and the UN .
Israel denies these claims and estimates that at least half of those killed are fighters , but did not provide any concrete evidence of this information .
on the Israeli side , 66 soldiers and six civilians , including one Thai worker , were killed .
Hamas and other fighters in Gaza fired 4,591 missiles and murderers during the fighting on Israeli cities , most in the south of the country .
meanwhile , the Israeli military carried out more than 5,000 air and other attacks .
the Israeli attacks damaged or destroyed thousands of houses in the Gaza Strip , and some 250,000 people sought refuge in more than 100 UN schools that were converted into temporary shelters .
while tens of thousands of people continue to live in the protected areas and the fighting continues , the education authorities postponed the start of the school year last week .
&quot; I hope the school will soon be reopened so that we can continue to learn , just as children in the world and Jewish children , &quot; said Mohammad Amara , a 13 @-@ year @-@ old boy who is currently living in a school in Gaza City .
