German economy shrinking by 0.2 % in spring
the crises around the globe have slowed down the German economy in the second quarter .
gross domestic product fell by 0.2 % from April to the end of June 2014 compared to the previous quarter .
this informed the Federal Statistical Office , confirming preliminary calculations .
consumption alone boosted the economy in the spring , while investment declined .
foreign trade also slowed the economy .
thanks to the strong annual start @-@ up , GDP growth for the first half of 2013 is 0.8 % higher than in the second half of 2013 .
