never said &quot; I love you &quot;
Henry was one of seven children of a family of Jamaica immigrants in Dudley in the Midlands in 1958 .
his father , who died when Henry 19 was worked in a factory and her relationship was limited .
Henry rehearses for a comedy , Rudy &apos;s Rare Records , which is partly based on an imaginary conversation with his father and emerged from the series on Radio 4 .
the soundtrack is a mix of reggae and rap , with lively melodies .
but Henry had to work through some difficult childhood moments .
he visited &quot; many &quot; therapies after the death of his mother , and Henry is concerned about his relationship with his father .
it was difficult to know him .
one never saw his face , only heard his voice : &quot; stop the crack .
let your sister in peace .
go ahead !
I want to look at cricket .
my older brothers Seymour and Hilton - who had already grown up when I was a child - went to the pub with him and talked about things like the form of beer glasses or the beauty of a cricket strike .
I never had such a conversation with him .
much of my life he was this serious type in the corner that the newspaper read .
Henry recently opened a foundry in Dudley , and although the conditions are better than at his father &apos;s time , he gained an insight into how life might have been for him .
it is now a bit brighter , but they are dark , smoked , deep stylist labyrinth with flames and smoke and a lot of soot .
my father put himself in the bath earlier and then he could be heard slowly how to sing because he could wash the foundry of himself .
when I walked around there , it became clear to me that he had done so for years to put the food on the table , and my respect for him increased .
however , Henry grew up as a child without love for his parents .
my father never surrounded me , he never said &quot; I love you . &quot;
only when my mother went badly towards the end of her life did we begin to say &quot; I love you , I love you , I love you . &quot;
through his own daughter Billie , with Dawn French , he could share the love he had missed as a child .
could you stop with &quot; I love you &quot; ?
stop embracing me !
Papa , I am 22 !
with Dawn French .
why should we not be friends ?
she is a great mother .
it is still friends with French , with whom he was married for 25 years .
Dawn is a good man .
why should we not be friends ?
she is a great mother .
Henry &apos;s mother was a diabetic .
this contributed to their death .
so when I became very , very overweight and showed symptoms of diabetes , my doctor said &quot; You must be radical .
so I went through this fitness and had to make a drastic diet to reverse the symptoms .
it is very difficult .
and it is tough .
nobody likes to eat carrots .
