the footprints left by Wolf and Fuchs two millennia ago in the footsteps of sound before they were burned .
in 2011 , the Land Monument Office had excavated the remains of a Roman villa in the Nord industrial park in Rheinbach .
they found walls of an economic building with a darre for drying grain and painting .
the building probably belonged to a Villa Rustica , an agricultural property , explained by archaeologist Dr. Jennifer Morscheiser .
a series of finds from these excavations presented them in a glass veil , including a large plate , several fine glass vessels and parts of a small shell .
the villa probably existed from the first to the fourth century after Christ , until the arrival of the Germans in the then Roman Rhineland , Morscheiser suspected .
