&quot; with the toll the Minister fails . &quot; Dobrindt wants to introduce a vignetting obligation on all German roads to start in 2016 .
however , domestic car owners may not be burdened by additional charges under the coalition agreement .
they should therefore receive full compensation for tolls via the car tax .
however , under EU law , the model must not discriminate against foreign drivers because of their nationality .
genetic disorder often misdiagnosed
a British woman says she thought as a result of misdiagnosis over many years that she would die .
Karin Rodgers lived almost all her youth in the belief that she had only a few years to live after having been diagnosed with another disease .
she actually suffered from Charcot @-@ Marie Tooth disease ( CMT ) - a group of inherited disorders that damage nerves outside the brain and spinal cord .
charity CMT UK announced that misdiagnoses are a common problem for people with CMT , because so little is known about this disease .
around 23,000 people in the UK are likely to suffer from CMT , which can lead to motor disorders such as muscle weakness , unsafe movement , and muddled toes .
the disease is incurable and progressive .
when Rodgers was 13 , she believed she was suffering from Friedreich @-@ Ataxie ( FA ) - a disease with very poor chances of survival .
Rodgers thought she would sit in the wheelchair before she would die 18 and before her 30th birthday .
the mother of two children who are 51 years old today said : &quot; as a child I knew I could not do the same as the others .
I always fell and everything took longer with me .
I could never drive with the other children wheelchair or skateboard and was often hired in school because of my way of going and running .
Rodgers said that at the age of 13 she saw her sickness records when her doctor left the room and read that she suffered from FA after several operations to relieve her Achilles and stretch her feet .
&quot; I felt guilty because I was curious , so I told nobody , but I went home , looking for the disease in the library and wrote to the FA Society , &quot; she said .
when I received an answer , I was shocked and terribly panic .
I thought I would be with 18 in the wheelchair and die with 25 , and between them all would slowly lose my skills .
I did all this alone with me and planned my own funeral .
she said , when she became 17 , she became clear that her abilities had not decreased as much as she had imagined and asked her doctor .
he simply stood up and surrounded me and said , &quot; my love , I do not think you have , otherwise you are already in the wheelchair . &quot;
I think you have something much less life @-@ threatening .
after some genetic tests she found CMT .
&quot; when he told me what CMT was , I felt like I was a winner , &quot; she said .
