smart ways to save at university textbooks
since the cost of university textbooks for many students is more than $ 1,000 per year , the fast @-@ second student Matt Schroeder considered a clever saving idea .
he invented a surrogacy system for higher @-@ semester students &quot; books and offered nominal compensation to delay resale .
&quot; my mathematical book usually costs $ 180 , but I got it for $ 10 for a semester and a Chick @-@ fil @-@ A @-@ Keks , &quot; said Schroeder , 19 who visited Covenant College in Georgia .
the books needed for the last semester would have cost him $ 430 , he said .
he spent $ 120 .
the collars told students that , on average , more than $ 1,200 per year spent on textbooks and study material , but there are different cost containment options for students .
online shops and creative approaches like Schroeders are increasingly the solution for students .
hiring textbooks is becoming more popular , so students can use a book for a semester , often at a much lower price than when buying .
Neebo Inc , which operates more than 250 university bookshops , announced that rent of textbooks had doubled since 2011 .
industry surveys show that about a quarter of the books were leased to college bookshops last spring , said Neebos Vice @-@ President Tevor Meyer .
according to the National Association of College Stores , less than half of all textbooks are bought in Campus bookshops .
here is the one @-@ off for the best deals .
buy online
some new books cost only one third of the price they are entitled to in the Campus bookshop .
the ninth edition of &quot; Calculus &quot; vno Ron Larwon , Bruce Edwards , and Robert Hostetler costs almost $ 290 , but can be purchased from the specialist bookmaker Chegg.com for $ 239.99 .
buy used
if you don &apos;t notice the notes of other or normal usage tracks , used books are a good option .
&quot; calculus &quot; is used on Chegg.com for $ 93.49 .
Matt Casaday , 25 , graduate student at Brigham Young University , says that he spent 42 cents on Amazon.com for a used edition of &quot; Strategic Media Decisions : understanding The Business End Of The Advertising Business . &quot;
the book was sold for $ 48 .
academics such as Ingrid Bracey , Head of the University of Massachusetts at Amherst College Without Walls , recommended students to ask their professors whether past spending was permissible .
sometimes the updates for the seminar work are not relevant .
in such cases , older editions can often be purchased for a fraction of the cost of the latest issue .
besides Chegg and Amazon , Half.com by eBay Inc is also a popular alternative for used books .
renting
the rental of textbooks is worth considering if you treat them reasonably well , remember to return them and do not want to keep the books after completing the course .
you can save more than 80 % of the cost of a newly purchased book .
a student could , for example , rent &quot; Calculus &quot; for the duration of a semester for about $ 20 .
find out about the terms and conditions of the business where you rent , including the penalty fees that may apply for the writing of notes , subtitles or utility papers .
if you do not return the book , the fees may even exceed the price of a new book .
e @-@ books
e @-@ books instead of traditional textbooks are also an option .
sometimes these books are de facto rented by providing an electronic licence for a certain period of time by wholesalers such as Amazon.com , Chegg and Barnes &amp; Noble Inc. .
at Chegg you can rent &quot; Calculus &quot; for 6 months for about 61 $ .
Bracey says that students in literature courses often find the best offers , since many classics can be downloaded free of charge nowadays , while scientific and engineering textbooks can be very expensive .
look around .
Joe Gault , 29 , who will shortly be attending the Pepperdine Law School , recommends the ISBN number for determining the price of books , as you can be sure to find the right textbook .
and before ordering online you should check whether the book is actually available .
he learned this lesson on the hard tour .
he bought a book that had four weeks delivery time and finally paid the full price at the College bookshop .
