blue Mountains teenagers flown
two young bushers were brought into safety with the rope winch after being caught overnight in the Blue Mountains in NSW .
the 16 @-@ year @-@ old girl and the 19 @-@ year @-@ old man broke on their tour shortly after Sunday afternoon in Govett Leap in Blackheath .
worried relatives called the police at about 20 o &apos;clock when the two had not returned home .
a conspiracy of local police and rescue services broke up and the couple was found around 23 : 00 near the Bridal Veil waterfalls .
the girl had wounded at her knees and the man had fallen and raised his head .
rescue forces remained with the couple overnight and they were flown out on Monday morning .
they were delivered to the Blue Mountains Hospital in a stable state with an ambulance .
anti @-@ government protests in Pakistan escalate
some 1000 demonstrators were pushed out of the PTV building by soldiers , said Information Minister Pervaiz Rashid .
after about half an hour the transmitter recorded the broadcast again .
PTV Director Athar Farooq said that the demonstrators equipped with sticks had damaged equipment in the editor .
dead or injured have not been reported .
the demonstrators are demanding the resignation of the prime minister , who is accused of electoral fraud .
the police told us that about a kilometre from Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif &apos;s residence , there was another clash of some 3000 demonstrators with security forces on Monday .
according to hospital information , a policeman was injured .
at the weekend , at least three people were killed and more than 500 injured when demonstrators tried to enter Sharif &apos;s residence .
they call for the resignation of the Prime Minister .
on Sunday evening , after a meeting in the army headquarters , the powerful military called for a political solution to the conflict , &quot; waste without time and without violence . &quot;
the Communication also said : &quot; the army remains committed to its role in ensuring the security of the state . &quot;
escalating violence has aroused concern for intervention by the military , which has already spread more frequently in the past .
the protests led by the opposition politician Imran Khan and the preacher Tahirul Qadri continue since the independence day on 14 August .
Sharif refuses to resign .
Khan and Qadri had called on their followers to stand out on Sunday .
&quot; we will not go back without having forced Sharif to resign , &quot; Khan said .
Qadri expressed similar views .
Khan accuses Sharif of winning the parliamentary election last May through fraud .
Qadri calls for the resignation of central and provincial governments .
then a transitional government should reform the electoral system and call for new elections .
more than 40 000 security forces are deployed to protect the government quarter .
the demonstrators were initially peacefully hiding before Parliament until Khan and Qadri called on them to enter Sharif &apos;s residence at the weekend .
