the Ruh
we showed a mighty tribe in our puzzle task of the summer series &quot; My piece of the Rhöner Glück &quot; last Friday .
several of these trees still exist in the district , the depicted copy is the &quot; Scourge Ruk &quot; above Unterweißenbrunn .
a hollow footpath leads up to the oak , which is 600 years old .
it &apos;s over Koppeln , Basaltsteinhaufen and Basaltsteinmeeren .
a piece below the quarry of Bauersberg , one kilometre north of the road to Weisbach , there is it .
Vital looks like the natural monument , it rises beyond the other trees in the area and reminds us of an American mammoth tree with an amount of more than eight metres .
a small Buddha on a tree grove suggests that this is a spiritual or mystical place .
but , despite intensive research , there were only indications of the name &apos;s future .
Dr. Wolfgang Schneider has also consulted the Bischofsheimer Archive and asked older people from Unterweißenbrunn to find out what Bewandtnis has with the Scourge .
the result of his investigations remained the rather sober explanation for the name .
thus , until about 80 years ago , the goat &apos;s brains were supposed to have driven their animals from Unterweißerbrunn to the laboriously roasted meadows freed from stones .
at the foot of the tree , the animal breeders exhausted by the ascent are said to have taken off .
in the meantime , the area has regained its importance , because goat herds actually grow again in the meadows .
the area has also been declared the core area of the biosphere reserve , Schneider has further identified .
you should be careful when entering the stone collections , because the basalt heated by the sun is also a popular place for cross @-@ country skiers .
a hiking path leads from Unterweißenbrunn to the tree , but it lies a little hidden .
further paths are signposted , descending towards Hochrhön and inviting you to an extensive hike .
where is the watershed ?
however , it is rare to find a watershed in our next task .
the mirroring in the tomb gives a good impression of the building , but we have some historical buildings in the district to which the building counter could fit .
where is our &quot; piece of Rhöner Glück &quot; ?
