after weeks of diving , Italy &apos;s prime minister and acting EU president , Matteo Renzi , won the nomination of his foreign minister Federica Mogherini as head of EU foreign policy , replacing Britin Catherine Ashton .
Renzi considers how the government @-@ run La Repubblica newspaper reflects , the appointment of his Mogherini , also considered a favorite in the government team , as a strengthening of the position of the Social Democrats and his own in the EU .
he also expects a boost to his &quot; reform package &quot; in Italy .
last but not least , Renzi hopes to calm down the left @-@ wing party base , which is constantly coming up against him , because Mogherini is assigned - albeit moderately - to it .
the dominant opinion in Rome is that of conservative representatives with President Jean @-@ Claude Juncker and Poland nominated as President of the Council , Donald Tusk .
the EU &apos;s chief diplomat will also represent President Juncker .
the pending approval of the European Parliament is considered certain .
otherwise , President Giorgio Napolitano would hardly have called the nomination of the 41st @-@ year politician of the ruling Democratic Party ( PD ) an &quot; important recognition &quot; of Italy &apos;s role in the EU .
la Repubblica spreads optimism that Mogherini , who has been leading party offices for almost two decades , will rise to the &quot; enormous challenges . &quot;
the native Roman is married and has two daughters .
her party career began in 1996 with the doctorate in the youth organization of the then Democratici di Sinistra ( Left Democrats ) , which joined the Catholic Center Party of Margherita in 2008 with today &apos;s Social Democratic PD .
in 1999 , Mogherini became Vice @-@ President of the European Community Organisation of Socialist Youth ( European Young Socialists ) for three years .
with the election in 2001 in the Party Council of the Left Democrats , she joined the high party politics , working in the foreign policy department of which she soon became head .
she has held traditional priorities of Italian foreign policy , such as the Middle East , with studies of NATO deployment in Afghanistan , in which Italy is involved with a contingent of troops , has maintained contacts with the Social Democrats in Europe and the Democrats in the United States .
she has been a member of the Chamber of Deputies since 2008 , where she is an expert in defence and European and international affairs .
when Renzi became Prime Minister in February 2014 , he met Mogherini as his Foreign Minister .
if the PD again has a better relationship today with the country &apos;s strong peace movement , which contributed to the party &apos;s more than 40 % vote in the EU elections in May , then Federica Mogherini , as it is noted in PD circles , will have a share in it .
the premises in Brussels that the new EU External Relations Officer has too little diplomatic experience , in other words , there is a lack of substance in the PD .
in Brussels , modestly realistic accents of Mogherini are being persecuted to the crisis in Ukraine , particularly by Poland and the Baltic members .
it supports the South Stream pipeline operated by the Russian company Gasprom , which is intended to transport Russian gas directly to southern Europe , bypassing Ukraine , which also serves Italy &apos;s energy security .
after Renzi took office as EU president in July , Mogherini travelled to Moscow for her first state visit .
photos they showed with Putin at the Shake hands were taken in Brussels with indignation , as well as inviting the Kremlin leader to a Milan economic summit in October .
