Norwegian Cruise just before a deal with Prestige Cruises of $ 3 billion
Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd NCHL.O , the third largest cruise operator in the world , is conducting advanced negotiations for the acquisition of rival Prestige Cruises International Inc for about $ 3 billion .
a deal would give Norwegian Cruise , a company worth $ 6.8 billion , access to the luxury cruise ships of Prestige Cruises and its wealthy clientele , while competing with larger rivals such as Royal Caribbean Cruises Ltd ( RCL.N ) and Carnival Corp ( CCL.N ) .
an agreement could already be announced this week , said the sources on Sunday and warned that the talks could end without results .
the owner of Prestige Cruises , the private equity company Apollo Global Management LLC ( APO.N ) also owns a 20 percent stake in Norwegian Cruise .
the sources asked to remain anonymous because the negotiations were not public .
representatives of Norwegian Cruise and Prestige Cruises did not respond to requests for comments , while a spokesman for Apollo rejected a comment .
Norwegian Cruise operates 13 cruise ships on routes between North America , the Mediterranean , the Baltic Sea , Central America and the Caribbean .
its revenues amounted to $ 2.57 billion in 2013 , an increase of 13 % compared to 2012 .
Prestige Cruises , also located in Miami , operates under the brand names Oceania and Regent , which jointly operate eight cruise ships on routes to Scandinavia , Russia , the Mediterranean , North America , Asia , Africa and South America .
it reported revenues for 2013 of $ 1.2 billion , an increase of 6 % compared to the previous year .
the cruise industry is around $ 29 billion overall and is expected to strengthen its middle class in emerging economies like China and India over the next few years .
the companies are trying to position themselves as the best choice for these new customers .
Prestige Cruises applied to US regulators in January 2014 .
Apollo is the majority shareholder in the company since a $ 850 million deal in 2007 .
Norwegian Cruise was formed in 2000 by a merger with a cruise operator owned by Genting Bhd ( GENT.KL ) , a leisure and casino company controlled by the Malaysian billionaire Lim Kok Thay .
Apollo invested $ 1 billion in Norwegian Cruise in 2008 .
Norwegian Cruise entered the stock exchange in January 2013 .
Genting , according to the approval authorities , held 28 % of the shares , Apollo 20 % of the shares and the private equity company TPG Capital LP a share of 8 % of the company .
Carnival , Royal Caribbean Cruises and Norwegian Cruise together have 82 % of passenger capacity on American cruise ships according to the original application documents for the Prestige Cruises stock exchange .
pro @-@ Hong Kong activists condemn China the day after the election decision .
a pekingtreue group turned near the Chinese flag .
on Sunday , the Standing Committee of the National People &apos;s Congress adopted a framework law allowing only two or three candidates for leadership in Hong Kong in 2017 .
all candidates must first obtain the majority support of a nominating committee that is likely to be filled with peking members .
this decision makes it almost impossible for opposition democrats to be allowed to vote and induced pro @-@ democracy activists to perceive their threat and to paralyse Hong Kong &apos;s financial center with &quot; Occupy Central &quot; protests .
political reform has long been a controversial issue in Hong Kong ; and China &apos;s party leaders fear that the call for democracy will spread to other cities .
after the publication of a Beijing White Paper , which set out China &apos;s dominance of Hong Kong in June , democracy activists held an unofficial referendum on the electoral process in the Special Administrative Region , where hundreds of thousands of people marched in the city &apos;s business district and organized a sit @-@ in .
Lis survey is organised by the Hong Kong Government and the Chinese Liaison Office in Hong Kong .
the Vice @-@ Chairman of the Legal Commission of the Standing Committee , Zhang Rongshun , and the Vice @-@ Director of the Hong Kong and Macao Office of the State Council , Feng Wei , should be consulted during the day .
student activists announced that they would meet in the afternoon before the Hong Kong leadership office .
Britain did not provide any democratic elements until the end of the 150 @-@ year colonial government in Hong Kong .
Putin calls on Kiev to start &quot; state talks &quot; with eastern Ukraine
Russian President Vladimir Putin , according to Russian media reports , called on Sunday for the Ukrainian government to stop fighting the separatists in the east of the country and to start negotiations directly on the &quot; statehood &quot; of the breakaway region .
his spokesman , Dimitri Peskov , later made it clear that Putin did not mean that the territory of eastern Ukraine under the control of the separatists would become part of Russia , but that his status with Ukraine should be redefined in order to give the Russian @-@ speaking region the power to represent its rights and interests .
Putin &apos;s call to the Kiev government to negotiate on an equal footing with pro @-@ Russian insurgents , however , fits in with the strategy that he seems to have pursued since the start of the riots five months ago : helping the separatists to capture territories and pressure the Ukrainian government to allow the newly proclaimed Novorossija region to become de facto independent of Russia .
in an interview with the state television channel One , Putin condemned the Ukrainian military campaign to reconquer the territories held by separatists in the eastern regions of Donezk and Luhansk , which were taken in March and April , after Moscow annexed the Ukrainian Crimea Peninsula on 18 March .
the Kremlin and the separatists have recently described the area as &quot; Novorossija &quot; or &quot; Neurussland , &quot; a term reminiscent of the pre @-@ revolutionary glory of the Russian empire .
Putin pointed out that all those who , as part of Ukrainian politicians &quot; campaigns for the elections on 26 October and , while government groups in the areas held by separatists , are attacking civilian communities for early peace talks &quot; caught in their illusions , &quot; Itar Tass said .
&quot; we need to start detailed talks immediately , not only on technical issues , but also on the political organisation of society and the state status of South @-@ East Ukraine in order to safeguard the interests of the people living there , &quot; he said .
Peskov said that Putin &apos;s reference to statehood must be seen in the context of the greater autonomy that Kiev &apos;s leaders have been discussing for months to dispel fears in Russian @-@ speaking areas that their cultural and linguistic rights are at risk .
only the Ukrainian Government can give the eastern territories the necessary autonomy , said Peskov .
this is not about negotiations between Ukraine and Russia , Peskov said , &quot; because it is not about a conflict between Russia and Ukraine , but about an internal conflict in Ukraine . &quot;
clarifying the Kremlin &apos;s &quot; misinterpretation &quot; of Putin &apos;s remarks underscored Russia &apos;s leadership in dealing with the separatist rebellion in the East , unlike the direct annexation of Crimea , where the majority of the two million inhabitants are ethnic Russians .
Moscow would have far greater difficulty in annexing the Donezk and Luhansk regions in eastern Ukraine , as most of the 6.5 million inhabitants are not Russians , and pre @-@ conflict surveys provided a broad majority for remaining in Ukraine .
the autonomy raised by Russian diplomats in international fora would give Ukraine &apos;s regional governments power to negotiate their own trade agreements and external relations , giving the Kremlin de facto control over an area that links Russia &apos;s territory with Crimea .
the Black Sea peninsula , annexed five months ago , is the home port for most of the Russian navy , as well as an important trading port and historic coastal region .
the regions between the Rostov area in Russia and Crimea are also rich in mines , factories and foundries that produce important components for the Russian military .
Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko suggested in his speech on the inauguration of office on 7 June that Ukrainian legislation , following new elections , should take into account the addition to the Constitution to give the respective territories greater control over their finances and languages .
but his idea of autonomy seems to be in sharp contrast to that of the Kremlin and the separatist rebels , who are accused of arming and inciting Moscow .
Putin &apos;s last call to Kyiv to negotiate with separatist leaders on an equal footing followed a further push by the rebels last week , after Russian troops and tanks invaded eastern Ukraine over the previously peaceful region along the Asov Sea .
the separatists supported by Russia took over the hands of Ukrainian security officials , who , according to fears of Ukrainian security officials , is the first step of a campaign to take over the strategic coastal region to Crimea , control of Nowoasowsk .
this is why massive civil and military preparations have begun to secure Mariupol , a steel industry with 500,000 inhabitants , between Nowoasowsk and the narrow access to Crimea Peninsula .
Poroshenko spoke at a meeting of the EU leadership in Brussels on Saturday and urged action to prevent further Russian aggression against Ukraine , a former Soviet republic that has been independent for 23 years .
&quot; we are close to a point where there is no return , &quot; said Poroshenko .
thousands of foreign troops and hundreds of foreign tanks are now on Ukraine &apos;s territory .
the EU summit did not take any concrete action , the leadership called for the draft of further sanctions against Russia to enter into force in the event of an unspecified escalation of the Ukrainian crisis .
Ukrainian soldiers had to withdraw from their positions in Ilowajsk after two Russian tanks and 1,000 soldiers invaded the Donetsk region last week to support the besieged separatists , said Colonel Andrij Lysenko , Speaker of the Ukrainian National Security and Defence Council Reimports in Kiev on Saturday .
on Sunday , the first 63 Ukrainian soldiers arrested by Russian incursion in Ilowajsk were replaced with 10 Russian parachutes captured in Ukrainian territory a week ago .
